Since I've done this more or less anyway, this journal is now officially friends only.  Comment here if you'd like to be added (and for those of you already on my f-list, I've already taken you into consideration).

Oh how I love being aspersed and maligned in other people's journals.  Just makes me feel all warm and fuzzy inside.  I also love how somebody who doesn't even really know me can feel comfortable calling me a bitch based upon a one-sided account of an incredibly complicated and terse situation.  Again, I'll reiterate my earlier observation - no matter what I do, it's not going to be acceptable.

Therefore, please, don't anybody do me any favors.  I am completely and irrevocably finished.

This is a question mainly for the straight girls (or guys) who read these entries, but have you ever found somebody of the same sex attractive in a non-sexual manner?  That is, have you ever looked at a person and thought objectively, "Wow...he/she is really good-looking" without necessarily wanting to shag them?  Now, I assure you, I'm most certainly not questioning my sexuality; I've done this for as long as I can remember and it can be somewhat attributed to the philosophy of aesthetics I suppose: the fact that human beings appreciate beauty in all its forms and seek it out.  I know this is a completely random and strange entry, but I was thinking about this today...and I was thinking about all the people I know who would judge me in a terrible manner if I ever told them "You know, so-and-so is really quite pretty".  Just goes to show who your real friends are...the ones who you can say anything to without fear of histrionics and high-horse judgement.

And...another have you ever...

Have you ever had a friend who brings nothing but bad news?  Who bitches constantly and wants sympathy but won't do anything to change their circumstances?  I'm beginning to believe in my astrology books more and more.
What do you really think of me?

I was very bad today. Didn't get anything productive done on my editorial...no, I just parked my fat ass in front of this computer and fiddled around with photoshop today. Reason? I found a new face for Rachel. Read: I succumbed to the pressure to make my character rather attractive. Well, not completely. I found a model that I could use who a.) had more than five pictures online and b.) whose page had not been removed from the webpage server. But honestly, why shouldn't I have an attractive character? Her looking the way she does now is not going to change the way I play her. It's not like she's going to, all of a sudden, start hitting on anything in trousers. I suppose I bowed before the mighty hand of conformity, however. Just about everybody's characters on RPG's are stunningly gorgeous. I don't really consider the person I chose as "stunningly gorgeous". She has a very "girl-next-door" feel to her. Which is exactly what I want as Rachel is a little tomboyish. The new Rachel can be seen on my AAH signature now. As well as in the picture behind I also made a bit of a disconcerting discovery as well today...but that's something you'd have to ask me about if you really care to know. It's not going here.

Well, it's been quite a while since I made an entry of any substance. The truth of the matter is, my holiday at home has been eventless and boring. Went to the dentist yesterday and now I have a very sore mouth. I had to get a tooth filled and when he went to give me the local anisthetic, he jabbed me in the wrong part of my gum, missing the vein, so he had to do it a second time. Needless to say I have a rather large bruise on my gum now. But that wasn't the only trauma of the visit. In order to keep the tooth dry that he was working on he used this little suction mechanism that looked like one of those squiggly straws with a fish-fin shaped attatchment on the end. Apparently it's supposed to fit between the cheek and gum. Uh, sure. If that's supposed to be true then I must have a small mouth or something because I have never been in so much pain in my life. And to top all of that off, the dentist's office called me at nine this morning to ask if I was doing ok after the appointment. I appreciate the call...but suffering from bouts of insomnia, I didn't hit the sack until about four in the morning and I didn't exactly relish only getting five hours of sleep. Oh well...I suppose there are worse things in life. I am currently awaiting Stark's reply as to what we're going to be doing with Rodolphus since he somehow ended up in Azkaban but Dolohov didn't. How does that work? Unless I misread OotP, the only Death Eater that escaped from the Ministry of Magic was Bellatrix as Voldemort took her with him. I find it a bit annoying that in my acceptance letter for Rodolphus I was told specifically that he was in Azkaban and wouldn't be receiving a trial because Lucius's trial was taking too long. When Miri got her acceptance letter, there was no mention of Dolohov being locked up at all. Grrr to that. I also know that people are growing restless with the prefect meeting, and I'm starting to run out of announcements...so...I need to talk to Anna about how much longer we're going to drag it out. I'll probably catch her on IM sometime tonight though (I hope). And in conclusion, a little quiz.

Remember, Lia, the other night when I asked you how tall a certain character should be?  Well I just found out the real-life person used to model him is approximately 6'6".  That's about nine inches taller than the other character.  That's one hell of a neck-strain.  *sigh*  Shall I go back and re-write certain passages, taking that into context?  Or just leave it?  And I thought 5'9" was fairly tall...
